    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that's helpful. I'm just struggling with the \"sneaky\" part. They sometimes bypass standard channels or hide information to get their own way, which feels a bit malicious or just fundamentally untrustworthy. Is there a way to describe that kind of \"under the radar\" or disruptive behavior in a formal way that doesn't make me sound like I'm just venting?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
